      • setOptionsToFields

        public void setOptionsToFields(java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> options,
                      java.lang.String fieldId)
        This method set options to field.
        Parameters:
        options - options which will be set to field. Key will be key and displayed value to user will be value, which is stored under concrete key.
        fieldId - id of field. It should has this notation: person.country.name, which mean that on variable person in root class and in their inner variable country and in their inner variable name will be set options.

      • setOptionsToFields

        public void setOptionsToFields(java.util.List<java.lang.String> options,
                      java.lang.String fieldId)
        This method set options to field.
        Parameters:
        options - options which will be set to field. Key and value which will be displayed to user will be the same.
        fieldId - id of field. It should has this notation: person.country.name, which mean that on variable person in root class and in their inner variable country and in their inner variable name will be set options.
